  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Civil & Structural Engineer (Design)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Roles & responsibilities:</strong></p><p>1. Coordination with Construction team/ Design Consultant/PE/Construction Subcontractor, etc. for Detail Design Development.</p><p>2. Review Structural Analysis and Calculation carried out by design consultant and develop simple structural calculation for temporary works</p><p>3. Planning relevant temporary civil structure, plan & section required for the Traffic diversion, such as Drain diversion, Retaining wall, Shop drawing development.</p><p>4. Review and planning for ERSS system for Underground structure using Diaphragm wall such as KP, Decking, and Strutting etc.</p><p>5. Check/Rectification of all the structural drawing/shop drawing if required.</p><p><strong>Requirements and relevant experience are as below:</strong></p><p>1. Bachelor’s / Master’s Degree of Civil Engineering or close discipline; <br /><br />2. Minimum 3 years of experience in Civil and Structural Engineering especially for LTA Project</p><p>3. Be well-aware of Traffic Diversion, Temp. Drain Diversion, and authority approval procedure</p><p>4. Be well-aware of Underground Structure/Construction Sequences and related civil design works.</p><p>5. Be well-aware of Eurocode, LTA CDC, and relevant design specification/standards.</p><p>* Candidates who has experience as CS Engineer (Design) in D&B contractor side would be an advantage.</p><p>* Interested applicants are required to submit their detailed CV and state their current and expected salary.</p>",
